WEBVTT

00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:05.400


00:00:07.721 --> 00:00:09.481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

00:00:37.938 --> 00:00:41.258
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

00:00:41.258 --> 00:00:43.145
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

00:00:57.505 --> 00:01:00.672
Why did you ask to see me?

00:01:00.672 --> 00:01:04.372
You've been featured on every TV program

00:01:04.372 --> 00:01:06.705
covering the Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

00:01:07.338 --> 00:01:09.338
You were involved
in the investigation too, right?

00:01:10.305 --> 00:01:14.638
I thought you might know
whether I'm the real killer or not.

00:01:15.305 --> 00:01:17.507
My opinion doesn't matter.

00:01:18.138 --> 00:01:21.238
Your DNA has already been identified,
Mr. Lee Yong Woo.

00:01:25.972 --> 00:01:27.572
I'm not sure about that...

00:01:30.172 --> 00:01:33.605
Why do you keep denying the crimes?

00:01:33.605 --> 00:01:36.305
The statute of limitations
has already expired,

00:01:36.305 --> 00:01:40.105
and you won't be punished for this anyway.

00:01:40.105 --> 00:01:43.305
Then why are the police digging up a case

00:01:43.305 --> 00:01:46.672
beyond the statute of limitations?

00:01:46.672 --> 00:01:49.338
You won't be able to convict me anyway.

00:01:50.805 --> 00:01:53.289
This isn't about convicting you.

00:01:55.172 --> 00:01:58.038
We just want to uncover the truth.

00:02:00.972 --> 00:02:02.872
Nine innocent victims,

00:02:02.872 --> 00:02:06.338
and their families
who were forced to let them go.

00:02:08.372 --> 00:02:09.972
On top of that,

00:02:11.805 --> 00:02:14.205
everyone who lived in Kangseng

00:02:14.972 --> 00:02:17.372
back then

00:02:18.005 --> 00:02:20.472
has the right to know the truth.

00:02:22.572 --> 00:02:25.672
Because it changed so much of their lives.

00:02:27.105 --> 00:02:28.745
Well,

00:02:28.745 --> 00:02:30.538
that makes sense.

00:02:38.505 --> 00:02:42.005
[Confession is the beginning of forgiveness,
and forgiveness opens the door to salvation]

00:02:42.005 --> 00:02:44.205
But still, it wasn't me.

00:02:45.738 --> 00:02:47.538
I didn't do it.

00:03:00.072 --> 00:03:01.872
All right then.

00:03:12.638 --> 00:03:14.405
Are you leaving already?

00:03:16.705 --> 00:03:18.605
I'll come again tomorrow.

00:03:33.505 --> 00:03:35.738
Stay out of my sight as much as possible.

00:03:35.738 --> 00:03:37.838
It won't take long!

00:03:37.838 --> 00:03:40.205
[Episode 2]
I don't plan on staying here long anyway.

00:03:42.738 --> 00:03:44.505
Kang Tae Joo!

00:03:49.305 --> 00:03:51.872
I'll take this case back.

00:03:55.038 --> 00:03:56.738
And you too.

00:03:57.638 --> 00:03:58.805
What?

00:03:58.805 --> 00:04:00.265
I will

00:04:00.265 --> 00:04:02.638
keep you by my side.

00:04:02.638 --> 00:04:04.338
Like back then.

00:04:07.038 --> 00:04:09.105
You psycho!

00:04:09.105 --> 00:04:12.472
I missed you, Kang Tae Joo.

00:04:23.338 --> 00:04:25.305
- You're splashing.
- Darn it.

00:04:26.538 --> 00:04:30.705
Tae Joo!

00:04:31.538 --> 00:04:35.238
Dead or alive?

00:04:35.238 --> 00:04:37.538
Alive!

00:04:37.538 --> 00:04:40.172
This is really not fun.

00:04:40.172 --> 00:04:42.072
Tae Joo!

00:04:42.072 --> 00:04:44.205
It's a joke, just a joke.

00:04:49.641 --> 00:04:51.205
- You punk!
- Hey, hey!

00:04:51.205 --> 00:04:53.405
Hold on, hold on!

00:05:01.372 --> 00:05:04.072
Were you scared? Afraid you got shot?

00:05:04.072 --> 00:05:05.138
You punk!

00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:06.538
How dare you try to shoot a prosecutor?

00:05:06.538 --> 00:05:08.472
Didn't you say we were friends?

00:05:08.472 --> 00:05:10.605
Since we are friends...

00:05:11.305 --> 00:05:13.305
why not...

00:05:13.305 --> 00:05:15.605
It's a joke, just a joke.

00:05:15.605 --> 00:05:17.638
A joke?

00:05:17.638 --> 00:05:19.369
Well?

00:05:19.369 --> 00:05:21.538
Not fun to you?

00:05:21.538 --> 00:05:23.172
It wasn't fun to me, either.

00:05:25.138 --> 00:05:28.172
Back then, your little jokes
weren't fun at all, either.

00:05:32.905 --> 00:05:35.401
[Period for Reporting and Surrendering Spies]

00:05:39.972 --> 00:05:42.972
I'll take this case back.

00:05:42.972 --> 00:05:44.605
And you too.

00:06:08.705 --> 00:06:10.305
Lee Seong Jin.

00:06:10.305 --> 00:06:11.849
I got

00:06:11.849 --> 00:06:13.538
released today.

00:06:14.238 --> 00:06:17.672
It's all thanks to you, Detective.

00:06:18.947 --> 00:06:21.738
[Kangseng Police Station]

00:06:21.738 --> 00:06:23.338
You've been through a lot.

00:06:25.605 --> 00:06:27.572
Live a proper life from now on.

00:06:28.372 --> 00:06:30.705
For your mother's sake, at least.

00:06:30.705 --> 00:06:32.338
Yes, sir.

00:06:33.038 --> 00:06:34.672
I'm really glad

00:06:36.172 --> 00:06:39.338
that you came back to Kangseng, Detective.

00:06:39.338 --> 00:06:41.897
I really wanted

00:06:41.897 --> 00:06:44.172
to tell you this.

00:06:46.761 --> 00:06:48.905
Bye.

00:06:55.005 --> 00:06:56.649
Well...

00:06:57.705 --> 00:06:58.972
Glad?

00:07:09.772 --> 00:07:14.205
It has now been confirmed that
the series of murders since October 1986

00:07:14.205 --> 00:07:17.257
are connected as a serial killing case.

00:07:17.257 --> 00:07:18.405
Yes?

00:07:18.405 --> 00:07:22.038
So how many cases are there in total?

00:07:22.038 --> 00:07:25.805
As far as we've confirmed so far,
there are four cases in total.

00:07:27.913 --> 00:07:31.538
- Go ahead.
- Why is this only being revealed now?

00:07:31.538 --> 00:07:34.905
Because the culprit's methods
changed slightly over time,

00:07:34.905 --> 00:07:38.005
it took time before we could
make an official announcement,

00:07:38.005 --> 00:07:41.272
but a joint police-prosecution task force
has already been formed.

00:07:41.272 --> 00:07:44.438
We are doing all we can
to apprehend the culprit.

00:07:46.105 --> 00:07:48.238
What do you mean the method changed?

00:07:48.238 --> 00:07:49.672
Mr. Hwang is so busy lately.

00:07:49.672 --> 00:07:50.805
I can barely see him.

00:07:50.805 --> 00:07:52.405
It's killing me too.

00:07:52.405 --> 00:07:55.938
All his other cases have been dumped on me.

00:07:55.938 --> 00:07:58.038
Handling the student protest cases alone
is enough of a headache.

00:07:58.038 --> 00:07:59.572
Why are you handling everything?

00:07:59.572 --> 00:08:01.272
What about Mr. Cha?

00:08:03.372 --> 00:08:04.605
Hand some of them over to me.

00:08:04.605 --> 00:08:06.738
No way. How could I possibly...

00:08:06.738 --> 00:08:08.772
It's okay. I've got plenty
of free time these days.

00:08:08.772 --> 00:08:10.805
This is exactly when
we should help each other out.

00:08:10.805 --> 00:08:12.838
Then, should I

00:08:12.838 --> 00:08:16.072
- take the protest case at least?
- Yeah, let him take it.

00:08:17.772 --> 00:08:20.172
I'd appreciate that if you would.

00:08:20.172 --> 00:08:21.772
Alright, then.

00:08:22.638 --> 00:08:24.072
It's been a long time.

00:08:24.072 --> 00:08:26.005
Make sure you get a good close shot.

00:08:26.005 --> 00:08:27.172
Stay for a meal.

00:08:27.172 --> 00:08:28.238
Reporters,

00:08:28.238 --> 00:08:30.872
lunch will be served at Seoul Hall
in the town center.

00:08:30.872 --> 00:08:32.305
- Okay.
- Thank you.

00:08:32.305 --> 00:08:33.938
Okay.

00:08:40.505 --> 00:08:42.105
I'm about to

00:08:42.105 --> 00:08:45.072
lay out a really great spread.

00:08:45.072 --> 00:08:47.472
But I don't like the guy holding the spoon.

00:08:47.472 --> 00:08:49.072
It takes all the fun out of it.

00:08:49.072 --> 00:08:51.772
Then give it to someone else.

00:08:54.605 --> 00:08:57.072
I might have to grab a spoon myself then.

00:08:57.072 --> 00:08:59.105
Well, are you hungry?

00:08:59.105 --> 00:09:01.038
No. I'm already full,

00:09:01.038 --> 00:09:03.405
thinking about the scoop I'm about to land.

00:09:03.405 --> 00:09:05.538
We're having a scoop?

00:09:05.538 --> 00:09:07.605
Clean your lens properly.

00:09:07.605 --> 00:09:10.705
You'll be photographing
the arrest of a serial killer.

00:09:10.705 --> 00:09:14.205
How would we know when or where
the suspect gets caught?

00:09:14.205 --> 00:09:16.372
I know who will catch him.

00:09:20.538 --> 00:09:22.372
Sir.

00:09:22.372 --> 00:09:23.405
I watched your press conference.

00:09:23.405 --> 00:09:25.505
Mr. Cha.

00:09:28.872 --> 00:09:33.272
Why did you choose me over Mr. Cha?

00:09:33.272 --> 00:09:37.638
I'm curious why you took the longer path
instead of the easy one.

00:09:38.738 --> 00:09:41.038
I'm pretty good at reading faces.

00:09:42.172 --> 00:09:44.572
Do I have a good one?

00:09:44.572 --> 00:09:46.153
More like

00:09:46.153 --> 00:09:49.472
that prosecutor over there
just doesn't look promising.

00:09:53.505 --> 00:09:56.172
Why? Is there something on my face?

00:09:56.172 --> 00:09:58.972
Huh? No, nothing.

00:09:58.972 --> 00:10:01.605
So, do you have something to say to me?

00:10:01.605 --> 00:10:04.472
Would you please make some time this evening?

00:10:04.472 --> 00:10:05.672
I have something to discuss with you.

00:10:05.672 --> 00:10:07.438
Ah, I'm not sure.

00:10:07.438 --> 00:10:10.572
My son's home for vacation.

00:10:10.572 --> 00:10:12.372
Cheol?

00:10:12.372 --> 00:10:15.872
Wow, he's already in college.

00:10:15.872 --> 00:10:17.272
Time flies!

00:10:17.272 --> 00:10:19.872
- It sure does.
- Bring him to the office sometime.

00:10:19.872 --> 00:10:21.272
I'd like to meet him.

00:10:21.272 --> 00:10:22.638
Yeah, maybe.

00:10:22.638 --> 00:10:25.105
Anyway, let's have that meal another time.

00:10:30.072 --> 00:10:32.338
"Mom is cooking," done writing?

00:10:32.338 --> 00:10:34.105
Yes!

00:10:34.105 --> 00:10:37.838
Number 3, "I played with my friend."

00:10:41.672 --> 00:10:44.372
"I played with my friend.'"

00:10:52.805 --> 00:10:53.838
Good job today.

00:10:53.838 --> 00:10:55.338
[Nurturing dreams with learning and love]
Alright, take care on your way.

00:10:55.338 --> 00:10:57.172
- I'll get going.
- Bye.

00:10:57.172 --> 00:10:58.805
Guys!

00:11:01.172 --> 00:11:03.138
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:11:23.538 --> 00:11:25.038
You almost got me there.

00:11:25.038 --> 00:11:26.605
Oh, that was so close.

00:11:26.605 --> 00:11:29.138
I thought I'd actually hit you this time.

00:11:29.138 --> 00:11:30.772
Have you eaten?

00:11:33.449 --> 00:11:35.038
Let's go grab something to eat.

00:11:36.472 --> 00:11:38.338
- I'm hungry.
- You're hungry?

00:11:38.338 --> 00:11:40.505
Yeah, with that growling.

00:11:41.972 --> 00:11:43.972
They say Tae Joo came back here.

00:11:44.872 --> 00:11:47.872
He came home completely wasted.

00:11:47.872 --> 00:11:50.138
Life was peaceful while he was away.

00:11:50.138 --> 00:11:53.105
Now to think about living
with him again is annoying.

00:11:54.138 --> 00:11:56.005
Then,

00:11:56.005 --> 00:11:57.605
want to live with me?

00:11:59.438 --> 00:12:01.272
Let's get married.

00:12:03.572 --> 00:12:07.172
Why are you proposing
in a rice soup restaurant?

00:12:07.172 --> 00:12:08.873
Don't say yes.

00:12:08.873 --> 00:12:11.005
It's not like that.

00:12:16.638 --> 00:12:18.605
Why aren't you answering?

00:12:20.905 --> 00:12:23.038
Don't you want to marry me?

00:12:23.038 --> 00:12:24.672
I'm not sure.

00:12:39.972 --> 00:12:43.172
Ma'am, I said no intestines.

00:12:43.172 --> 00:12:44.972
Oh dear, I forgot.

00:12:44.972 --> 00:12:48.205
What to do?
I can't swap it now that it's served.

00:12:48.205 --> 00:12:49.405
I'll just eat it.

00:12:49.405 --> 00:12:51.138
Sorry.

00:12:53.138 --> 00:12:54.772
Wait.

00:12:58.472 --> 00:13:00.938
I'm not asking you to decide right now.

00:13:04.772 --> 00:13:07.238
Think about it carefully.

00:13:08.405 --> 00:13:10.005
Wait a moment.

00:13:11.838 --> 00:13:13.605
There.

00:13:14.772 --> 00:13:16.372
Here.

00:13:17.805 --> 00:13:18.838
Go on, have some.

00:13:18.838 --> 00:13:20.438
You have some too.

00:13:31.005 --> 00:13:34.172
Why are you moping alone?

00:13:35.138 --> 00:13:36.738
Is something wrong?

00:13:37.638 --> 00:13:39.238
Sang Beom.

00:13:40.372 --> 00:13:41.805
Tae Joo is back.

00:13:41.805 --> 00:13:43.472
Kang Tae Joo?

00:13:44.805 --> 00:13:46.905
Wait, that punk is here?

00:13:53.238 --> 00:13:56.138
Darn it.

00:13:56.138 --> 00:13:59.538
He's not going to start cracking down
around here again, is he?

00:13:59.538 --> 00:14:02.405
You little punk, you scared?

00:14:02.405 --> 00:14:06.238
Well, it's not that I'm scared,
but he's a bit...

00:14:06.238 --> 00:14:09.938
Anyway, be careful.
He's not someone to mess with.

00:14:09.938 --> 00:14:12.338
Back then at least we knew his weakness.

00:14:12.338 --> 00:14:15.572
If it's a weakness, we can find another one.

00:14:15.572 --> 00:14:17.472
That's right.

00:14:19.505 --> 00:14:21.672
[Kangseng Police Station]

00:14:21.672 --> 00:14:23.238
Let's start by finding the victims.

00:14:23.238 --> 00:14:26.572
But are there any surviving victims?
There aren't any.

00:14:26.572 --> 00:14:29.572
No, there haven't been
any attempted murder cases yet.

00:14:29.572 --> 00:14:32.972
- Exactly.
- He abducts, rapes, and then kills.

00:14:32.972 --> 00:14:35.105
What if things went wrong
before it went all the way?

00:14:35.105 --> 00:14:37.538
Attempted kidnapping, or attempted rape?

00:14:37.538 --> 00:14:38.838
Or rape.

00:14:38.838 --> 00:14:40.672
There's no way there'd be anything like that.

00:14:40.672 --> 00:14:42.372
That punk is human too.

00:14:42.372 --> 00:14:44.805
You think he never makes mistakes?

00:14:46.405 --> 00:14:49.672
Alright, start by looking for any sex crimes
in Kangseng over the past two years

00:14:49.672 --> 00:14:52.738
that bear even the slightest
resemblance to this case.

00:14:52.738 --> 00:14:55.338
Any unusual details?

00:14:55.338 --> 00:14:58.238
- When meeting victims of sexual crimes,
- I don't know.

00:14:58.238 --> 00:15:00.438
make sure to bring along a female officer.

00:15:04.405 --> 00:15:06.005
Thank you.

00:15:08.472 --> 00:15:10.372
Where are we going next?

00:15:11.338 --> 00:15:14.305
The end of...

00:15:14.305 --> 00:15:16.505
this alley.

00:15:16.505 --> 00:15:18.472
Okay, let's go.

00:15:22.105 --> 00:15:25.538
There must be a witness
among them who saw him.

00:15:38.572 --> 00:15:40.772
- Thank you.
- Eat a lot.

00:15:40.772 --> 00:15:42.105
Oh my, Mom.

00:15:42.105 --> 00:15:44.405
Looks like you really
like your second daughter-in-law.

00:15:44.405 --> 00:15:45.738
I know, right?

00:15:45.738 --> 00:15:48.638
Mother, you're making me feel left out.

00:15:48.638 --> 00:15:51.305
There's nothing to feel left out about.

00:15:51.305 --> 00:15:54.921
Oh dear, you should hurry
and have a baby first.

00:15:54.921 --> 00:15:56.905
Mom.

00:15:56.905 --> 00:15:58.072
Why talk about babies?

00:15:58.072 --> 00:16:00.405
Even Ki Hwan doesn't have one yet.

00:16:00.405 --> 00:16:03.538
Have a smart kid
who takes after you instead of him.

00:16:03.538 --> 00:16:04.738
That way you won't suffer.

00:16:04.738 --> 00:16:08.938
This one's all grown physically
but still just a kid.

00:16:08.938 --> 00:16:12.572
Mom, you said I was your favorite, remember?

00:16:12.572 --> 00:16:16.272
Ki Beom, did you properly
introduce yourself to Tae Joo?

00:16:17.005 --> 00:16:18.672
Not yet.

00:16:19.672 --> 00:16:23.872
Why? Does Tae Joo not like him?

00:16:23.872 --> 00:16:26.538
No, it's just that
he hasn't hardly been home lately.

00:16:26.538 --> 00:16:30.372
Well, with that serial killer case,
he must be swamped.

00:16:30.372 --> 00:16:31.938
Yeah.

00:16:31.938 --> 00:16:35.272
What kind of bad omen is this
with a wedding coming up?

00:16:35.272 --> 00:16:39.638
The bride's family should set the date.

00:16:39.638 --> 00:16:42.072
Go introduce yourself properly first.

00:16:42.072 --> 00:16:43.138
Got it?

00:16:43.138 --> 00:16:44.738
Got it.

00:16:51.491 --> 00:16:53.172
Well...

00:16:53.172 --> 00:16:55.172
What if Tae Joo doesn't like me?

00:16:55.172 --> 00:16:56.505
Doesn't like you?

00:16:56.505 --> 00:16:58.272
No way.

00:16:58.272 --> 00:17:01.805
He might care about me as his friend's
brother, but maybe not as his brother-in-law.

00:17:01.805 --> 00:17:04.438
I don't even have a decent job.

00:17:05.272 --> 00:17:07.017
Honestly,

00:17:07.017 --> 00:17:09.672
you are too good for me.

00:17:09.672 --> 00:17:11.638
I'm the one who hit the jackpot.

00:17:14.072 --> 00:17:15.705
Lee Ki Beom.

00:17:16.405 --> 00:17:18.738
How many teachers do you think
there are in Kangseng?

00:17:19.605 --> 00:17:21.385
I don't know.

00:17:21.385 --> 00:17:22.409
About a hundred?

00:17:22.409 --> 00:17:24.605
Teachers are common.

00:17:24.605 --> 00:17:27.205
Then in Kangseng,

00:17:27.205 --> 00:17:30.205
how many men are as handsome as Andy Lau?

00:17:33.105 --> 00:17:34.838
Just you.

00:17:34.838 --> 00:17:38.438
I'm the one who hit the jackpot, got it?

00:17:41.005 --> 00:17:42.472
Comparing me to Andy Lau is a bit much.

00:17:42.472 --> 00:17:45.505
Why? I think you're way more handsome.

00:17:45.505 --> 00:17:47.305
- Really?
- Yes!

00:17:49.571 --> 00:17:50.825
[Kangseng Police Station]
Hey.

00:17:52.972 --> 00:17:54.838
Your socks and underwear.

00:17:54.838 --> 00:17:57.572
You should've brought more.

00:17:57.572 --> 00:17:59.538
How long are you gonna be away?

00:17:59.538 --> 00:18:01.605
Go home now.

00:18:01.605 --> 00:18:04.172
What kind of clothes are these?

00:18:04.172 --> 00:18:08.738
Don't walk alone at night.
I'll tell Ki Beom to walk you home.

00:18:08.738 --> 00:18:10.572
Already did.

00:18:10.572 --> 00:18:13.705
Really? That's sweet of him.

00:18:13.705 --> 00:18:15.372
Since when?

00:18:15.372 --> 00:18:17.938
Maybe about three years?

00:18:19.405 --> 00:18:20.638
Are you two dating?

00:18:20.638 --> 00:18:22.438
We're getting married.

00:18:25.097 --> 00:18:28.572
You'll come to my wedding, right?

00:18:28.572 --> 00:18:30.005
When is it?

00:18:30.005 --> 00:18:32.972
You pick the date. Whatever works for you.

00:18:32.972 --> 00:18:34.605
- Wait...
- Gotta go.

00:18:40.072 --> 00:18:41.372
- Hello.
- Oh.

00:18:41.372 --> 00:18:43.005
Hello, how are you?

00:18:43.005 --> 00:18:45.338
What's going on?

00:18:45.338 --> 00:18:47.017
She told me

00:18:47.017 --> 00:18:48.572
to set the date.

00:18:48.572 --> 00:18:49.905
The date for what?

00:18:49.905 --> 00:18:51.472
My little sister's wedding day.

00:18:51.472 --> 00:18:53.438
- She's getting married?
- Seems so.

00:18:53.438 --> 00:18:55.305
That's great news, congrats. And?

00:18:55.305 --> 00:18:58.972
Well, I've only ever caught criminals,
but I've never set a wedding date.

00:18:59.972 --> 00:19:03.472
Isn't it kind of similar
to catching a criminal?

00:19:03.472 --> 00:19:04.672
Really?

00:19:04.672 --> 00:19:07.272
What are you idiots even talking about?

00:19:07.272 --> 00:19:09.638
Do you want to mess up
such an important family event?

00:19:09.638 --> 00:19:11.338
- For a special day like that,
- Yeah.

00:19:11.338 --> 00:19:13.705
you go to a good fortune-teller

00:19:13.705 --> 00:19:17.205
and set an auspicious date.

00:19:17.205 --> 00:19:19.305
Pay them well.

00:19:22.072 --> 00:19:24.438
Well... Detective Kang.

00:19:24.438 --> 00:19:26.605
I have something to tell you.

00:19:27.272 --> 00:19:29.472
Alright.

00:19:29.472 --> 00:19:32.041
About a month ago,

00:19:32.041 --> 00:19:33.172
on her way home,

00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:36.338
she said she was abducted by a man.

00:19:37.105 --> 00:19:40.072
With her hands tied behind her back.

00:19:48.538 --> 00:19:52.772
Please help me!

00:19:52.772 --> 00:19:56.905
Please help me!

00:19:59.538 --> 00:20:01.929
Please save me...

00:20:01.929 --> 00:20:03.605
- Oh my.
- Oh, no. Are you alright?

00:20:03.605 --> 00:20:04.905
Honey, call the police!

00:20:04.905 --> 00:20:06.005
Call the police?

00:20:06.005 --> 00:20:09.172
Miss, can you stand up?

00:20:10.593 --> 00:20:12.297
[Police]

00:20:12.938 --> 00:20:15.672
I don't want to report it.

00:20:15.672 --> 00:20:17.738
What? Why not?

00:20:17.738 --> 00:20:20.605
I'm too scared to do it.

00:20:20.605 --> 00:20:26.072
She refused firmly,
so we just escorted her home.

00:20:26.072 --> 00:20:29.138
So that's why there's no record.

00:20:29.138 --> 00:20:31.872
Her hands were tied behind her back

00:20:31.872 --> 00:20:33.972
with a handkerchief too.

00:21:03.572 --> 00:21:06.172
I'm sure I told you

00:21:06.172 --> 00:21:08.238
that I didn't want to report it.

00:21:08.238 --> 00:21:09.305
Well, about that...

00:21:09.305 --> 00:21:11.938
Nothing actually happened.

00:21:11.938 --> 00:21:13.338
Really.

00:21:13.338 --> 00:21:15.838
- But you said you were abducted.
- That's...

00:21:18.138 --> 00:21:20.372
But I didn't die.

00:21:20.372 --> 00:21:22.972
And nothing terrible happened.

00:21:24.905 --> 00:21:26.872
You were lucky.

00:21:32.338 --> 00:21:36.105
What kind of 'lucky' woman
goes through something like that?

00:21:36.105 --> 00:21:40.538
I can't even be alone at night
because of what happened that day.

00:21:40.538 --> 00:21:44.072
If a stranger talks to me,
my whole body freezes.

00:21:44.072 --> 00:21:46.405
I can't live normally anymore.

00:21:47.172 --> 00:21:49.305
And you call that 'lucky'?

00:21:49.305 --> 00:21:51.205
After all, the other victims

00:21:52.872 --> 00:21:55.072
didn't survive.

00:21:56.972 --> 00:21:58.938
But you did, Ms. Park Ae Sook.

00:22:00.521 --> 00:22:02.313
My goodness.

00:22:08.405 --> 00:22:10.038
That day,

00:22:10.738 --> 00:22:14.238
I was on my way back from a blind date.

00:22:17.105 --> 00:22:19.872
We were supposed to have some tea,

00:22:19.872 --> 00:22:22.838
but it turned into dinner and went long.

00:22:28.338 --> 00:22:31.305
He was a nice guy.

00:22:31.305 --> 00:22:34.738
I thought luck was finally
on my side that day.

00:22:36.738 --> 00:22:38.441
Did you

00:22:38.441 --> 00:22:41.505
happen to see something like a scarecrow?

00:22:44.205 --> 00:22:46.472
I think I did.

00:23:02.938 --> 00:23:04.638
Where are your stockings?

00:23:06.697 --> 00:23:08.329
I...

00:23:08.329 --> 00:23:09.577
Darn it.

00:23:09.577 --> 00:23:10.672
Yes...

00:23:10.672 --> 00:23:13.005
Yes, I have stockings.

00:23:13.005 --> 00:23:16.605
I took them off because they were torn.

00:23:16.605 --> 00:23:18.872
They're in my purse, I swear.

00:23:18.872 --> 00:23:19.905
Your purse?

00:23:19.905 --> 00:23:22.405
I dropped it over there earlier.

00:23:26.572 --> 00:23:27.638
Stay here.

00:23:27.638 --> 00:23:29.338
Okay.

00:23:39.905 --> 00:23:41.872
I just knew

00:23:41.872 --> 00:23:45.238
if I didn't run then, I would die.

00:23:50.772 --> 00:23:52.938
I was so scared.

00:23:52.938 --> 00:23:56.338
Afraid that man would come back any moment.

00:23:56.338 --> 00:23:59.205
Oh dear, what on earth happened?

00:23:59.205 --> 00:24:00.238
Are you alright?

00:24:00.238 --> 00:24:03.005
Honey, call the police!

00:24:03.005 --> 00:24:05.005
Miss, can you stand up?

00:24:13.838 --> 00:24:16.572
Did you see the suspect's face?

00:24:17.772 --> 00:24:20.105
I avoided eye contact.

00:24:20.105 --> 00:24:22.038
I thought he'd kill me if I didn't.

00:24:24.072 --> 00:24:26.105
I know this is hard,

00:24:26.105 --> 00:24:28.457
but is there anything else?

00:24:28.457 --> 00:24:30.172
Anything you remember helps.

00:24:32.605 --> 00:24:35.505
He was thin.

00:24:35.505 --> 00:24:37.838
Average height?

00:24:38.505 --> 00:24:40.838
Just ordinary.

00:24:42.805 --> 00:24:47.005
Did you not report it
because you feared retaliation?

00:24:50.105 --> 00:24:52.538
My purse was gone.

00:24:53.872 --> 00:24:55.705
The suspect probably took it, right?

00:24:55.705 --> 00:24:58.738
My ID was in there.

00:24:58.738 --> 00:25:02.138
That means he's got my name and address.

00:25:03.305 --> 00:25:04.809
So

00:25:04.809 --> 00:25:07.038
how could I report it?

00:25:19.738 --> 00:25:22.372
Like you said, Ms. Park,

00:25:22.372 --> 00:25:25.438
maybe you weren't lucky after all.

00:25:26.305 --> 00:25:30.105
You went through something
you shouldn't have, like the other victims.

00:25:30.105 --> 00:25:33.172
But what saved you then

00:25:33.172 --> 00:25:35.872
wasn't luck, but yourself.

00:25:39.338 --> 00:25:41.505
Your courage, Ms. Park.

00:25:52.338 --> 00:25:55.905
When we catch him,
you'll be the first to know.

00:25:55.905 --> 00:25:57.838
One more thing,

00:25:57.838 --> 00:26:01.072
I'm not sure if this helps,

00:26:02.005 --> 00:26:04.672
but that man's hand...

00:26:05.738 --> 00:26:10.272
It felt soft... like a woman's hand.

00:26:20.072 --> 00:26:23.105
[Kangseng Bookstore]

00:26:33.138 --> 00:26:34.938
Hello.

00:26:35.705 --> 00:26:37.505
I'm here

00:26:37.505 --> 00:26:41.172
to pick up a reference book,

00:26:43.238 --> 00:26:45.272
under Yu Jeong Rin.

00:26:47.105 --> 00:26:49.905
You are not Yu Jeong Rin.

00:26:53.138 --> 00:26:55.258
Do you remember

00:26:55.258 --> 00:26:57.805
Jeong Rin?

00:26:57.805 --> 00:26:59.405
Yes.

00:27:07.272 --> 00:27:10.105
Hey, why are you crying?

00:27:11.305 --> 00:27:12.905
Are you okay?

00:27:15.139 --> 00:27:16.672
[Map]

00:27:16.672 --> 00:27:18.772
It should be around here,

00:27:18.772 --> 00:27:20.005
where Ms. Park met him.

00:27:20.005 --> 00:27:22.772
It was a month
before Yu Jeong Rin was murdered.

00:27:22.772 --> 00:27:26.672
Like you said, he's truly
obsessed with stockings.

00:27:26.672 --> 00:27:28.672
He's a complete psycho.

00:27:36.638 --> 00:27:38.838
He hides in places like this.

00:27:52.272 --> 00:27:56.073
He waits and waits

00:27:56.073 --> 00:27:58.105
for the right target.

00:28:11.905 --> 00:28:14.105
Then he makes his move.

00:28:16.872 --> 00:28:21.172
If he gets spotted,
he plays dead like a scarecrow.

00:28:26.305 --> 00:28:28.338
And when the distance closes,

00:28:29.438 --> 00:28:31.072
he attacks.

00:28:33.672 --> 00:28:36.038
We'll never catch him with patrols alone.

00:28:36.038 --> 00:28:37.905
Then...

00:28:37.905 --> 00:28:39.572
We make him come to us on his own.

00:28:39.572 --> 00:28:41.738
Get everyone
to the conference room. Right now!

00:28:41.738 --> 00:28:43.338
Yes, sir.

00:28:49.772 --> 00:28:51.805
How could that happen?

00:28:51.805 --> 00:28:53.609
Jeong Rin

00:28:53.609 --> 00:28:57.138
always kept her promises.

00:28:57.138 --> 00:29:01.372
She must've wanted to keep her promise to you

00:29:01.372 --> 00:29:03.705
about coming to buy the reference books.

00:29:04.605 --> 00:29:06.633
Jeong Rin

00:29:06.633 --> 00:29:08.138
had such a good friend.

00:29:10.105 --> 00:29:12.005
Mister.

00:29:12.005 --> 00:29:13.605
Yeah?

00:29:15.472 --> 00:29:18.872
Could you at least remember Jeong Rin's name?

00:29:21.272 --> 00:29:22.905
Me?

00:29:24.338 --> 00:29:27.105
Jeong Rin would've liked that.

00:29:31.438 --> 00:29:33.138
Alright.

00:29:36.772 --> 00:29:38.305
Want more?

00:29:38.305 --> 00:29:39.938
Yes, please.

00:29:44.905 --> 00:29:46.838
That's...

00:29:48.937 --> 00:29:50.238
[Please claim your lost items]

00:29:50.238 --> 00:29:52.515
Someone must've left it,
but no one's come for it.

00:29:55.272 --> 00:29:59.105
Is there any ID inside? Or a wallet?

00:29:59.105 --> 00:30:00.605
I haven't opened it.

00:30:00.605 --> 00:30:03.038
It's someone else's purse,
so rummaging through it feels wrong.

00:30:03.038 --> 00:30:05.105
Well, they'll come get it, right?

00:30:08.072 --> 00:30:10.805
You must be getting busy
with the wedding prep.

00:30:10.805 --> 00:30:13.353
You've been thinking about your mother
a lot lately, haven't you?

00:30:13.353 --> 00:30:17.138
She would be so happy
if she were still alive.

00:30:17.138 --> 00:30:18.138
You think so?

00:30:18.138 --> 00:30:20.105
- Of course.
- Good work.

00:30:20.739 --> 00:30:22.538
Let's have a meal sometime.

00:30:22.538 --> 00:30:25.417
Who is that? Even the principal
came out to greet him.

00:30:25.417 --> 00:30:27.205
This way.

00:30:27.205 --> 00:30:29.172
Ms. Kang Sun Young?

00:30:32.338 --> 00:30:34.438
That's you, right?

00:30:34.438 --> 00:30:37.938
Wow, didn't expect to see you here.

00:30:37.938 --> 00:30:40.705
It's been a really long time,
hasn't it? Right?

00:30:41.321 --> 00:30:42.972
Do you know me?

00:30:42.972 --> 00:30:45.472
Of course, I do.

00:30:45.472 --> 00:30:49.305
Well, you might not remember me.

00:30:49.305 --> 00:30:51.338
It's been so long.

00:30:59.738 --> 00:31:03.472
Oh my, you must be busy,
yet you even took interest in our school.

00:31:03.472 --> 00:31:06.072
[Honesty, integrity, and diligence]
I don't know how to thank you.

00:31:06.072 --> 00:31:07.638
This is my alma mater.

00:31:07.638 --> 00:31:10.105
I'm happy to be of help.

00:31:10.105 --> 00:31:11.238
And the county head is doing well, I hope?

00:31:11.238 --> 00:31:14.072
My uncle is always busy.

00:31:14.072 --> 00:31:16.438
I'll arrange a meeting sometime soon.

00:31:16.438 --> 00:31:17.505
Sounds good.

00:31:17.505 --> 00:31:22.005
By the way, how do you know Ms. Kang?

00:31:22.005 --> 00:31:23.838
She's my friend's younger sister.

00:31:23.838 --> 00:31:25.472
Oh, I see.

00:31:25.472 --> 00:31:29.738
He's my high school buddy,
and he is a cop now.

00:31:29.738 --> 00:31:32.405
Both siblings turned out well,

00:31:32.405 --> 00:31:34.938
given their family's situation.

00:31:34.938 --> 00:31:36.938
Family situation?

00:31:39.938 --> 00:31:43.038
[Service, courtesy, and order]
Hey, everyone's here, right?

00:31:43.038 --> 00:31:44.672
Well...

00:31:46.572 --> 00:31:48.905
What are you talking about?

00:31:48.905 --> 00:31:51.005
Why should we deal with some student protest?

00:31:51.005 --> 00:31:54.272
That's not even our jurisdiction!

00:31:54.272 --> 00:31:56.872
The Olympics are next week.

00:31:56.872 --> 00:31:58.572
Jurisdiction doesn't matter now.

00:31:58.572 --> 00:32:01.738
We get deployed
based on the size of the protest.

00:32:01.738 --> 00:32:04.138
Why do you keep changing what you're saying?

00:32:04.138 --> 00:32:06.972
Weren't we supposed
to be excluded for a while?

00:32:06.972 --> 00:32:08.605
Mr. Heo, you heard that too, right?

00:32:08.605 --> 00:32:09.905
Yes, that's right.

00:32:09.905 --> 00:32:11.705
I don't know, either.

00:32:11.705 --> 00:32:13.238
They say it's the new prosecutor in charge.

00:32:13.238 --> 00:32:15.638
They're cracking down hard.
What am I supposed to do about it?

00:32:15.638 --> 00:32:17.638
Who's the prosecutor in charge?

00:32:18.372 --> 00:32:20.649
[Protect civic order, build a bright society]
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!

00:32:20.649 --> 00:32:23.005
Military regime, step down!

00:32:23.005 --> 00:32:25.105
[Eradicate corruption]
Step down! Step down!

00:32:25.105 --> 00:32:29.305
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!
Military regime, step down!

00:32:29.305 --> 00:32:31.238
Step down! Step down!

00:32:31.238 --> 00:32:35.438
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!
Military regime, step down!

00:32:35.438 --> 00:32:37.505
[Protect civic order, build a bright society]
Step down! Step down!

00:32:37.505 --> 00:32:39.305
Down with dictatorship! Fight for democracy!

00:32:39.305 --> 00:32:41.672
- You're back?
- Whatever.

00:32:41.672 --> 00:32:44.872
Chasing 'reds' by day

00:32:44.872 --> 00:32:47.305
and murderers by night.

00:32:47.305 --> 00:32:49.172
I'm dead tired.

00:32:49.172 --> 00:32:51.472
Would be perfect if the killer
were among them.

00:32:51.472 --> 00:32:52.905
Military regime, step down!

00:32:52.905 --> 00:32:55.672
- Let's go, back to work.
- Step down! Step down!

00:33:05.155 --> 00:33:07.178
- Forward!
- Move forward!

00:33:34.772 --> 00:33:35.772
What is this?

00:33:35.772 --> 00:33:37.438
What's going on?

00:33:50.051 --> 00:33:52.195
[Espionage, Crime, Disaster,
Reporting Center]

00:35:00.238 --> 00:35:01.838
You punk!

00:35:07.205 --> 00:35:08.905
You little...

00:35:09.737 --> 00:35:12.705
- Let go.
- Are you going to kill him?

00:35:12.705 --> 00:35:14.438
What's the big deal? He's a commie.

00:35:14.438 --> 00:35:16.238
Let go!

00:35:16.238 --> 00:35:17.538
What are you doing?

00:35:17.538 --> 00:35:18.538
What are you doing right now?

00:35:18.538 --> 00:35:20.272
Act like a proper cop!

00:35:20.272 --> 00:35:21.705
Not some thug with a badge!

00:35:21.705 --> 00:35:23.605
Are you done talking, you punk?

00:35:23.605 --> 00:35:25.072
Am I wrong?

00:35:25.072 --> 00:35:26.672
You're acting like a street punk.

00:35:26.672 --> 00:35:29.105
And what about you?
You got kicked out of Seoul!

00:35:29.105 --> 00:35:31.705
Just do what you're told, you punk!

00:35:31.705 --> 00:35:34.472
For God's sake, get a grip!

00:35:34.472 --> 00:35:38.238
Hey! Stop right there, you punk!

00:35:39.337 --> 00:35:40.438
Darn it!

00:35:40.438 --> 00:35:42.105
Hey!

00:35:44.005 --> 00:35:45.638
We have to go.

00:35:49.238 --> 00:35:50.838
This way!

00:36:01.905 --> 00:36:04.105
It's definitely Ki Beom.

00:36:05.172 --> 00:36:07.105
Why would he...

00:36:08.172 --> 00:36:10.038
Hey, you punk!

00:36:10.038 --> 00:36:12.172
I lost him because of you!

00:36:12.172 --> 00:36:13.905
Lost him?

00:36:15.747 --> 00:36:17.038
Darn it!

00:36:17.038 --> 00:36:18.638
How could you lose him?

00:36:18.638 --> 00:36:21.138
Detective Do, I told you!

00:36:21.138 --> 00:36:22.272
We can't afford to lose him.

00:36:22.272 --> 00:36:25.172
I'm sorry, sir.

00:36:25.172 --> 00:36:26.905
What are you waiting for? Go after him.

00:36:26.905 --> 00:36:28.738
Yes, sir.

00:36:31.238 --> 00:36:32.705
Was it you?

00:36:32.705 --> 00:36:35.372
The one who pulled our station officers here?

00:36:35.372 --> 00:36:36.838
Do you have any idea
what we're working on right now?

00:36:36.838 --> 00:36:40.838
This is just as serious
as the serial killings.

00:36:40.838 --> 00:36:43.572
It's a matter of national security!

00:36:44.838 --> 00:36:46.409
Don't you ever

00:36:46.409 --> 00:36:48.838
drag our detectives into this again.

00:36:50.638 --> 00:36:52.272
Detective Kang.

00:36:52.972 --> 00:36:55.272
You keep forgetting.

00:36:55.272 --> 00:36:57.038
I'm the prosecutor

00:36:57.038 --> 00:36:59.172
before I'm your friend.

00:36:59.907 --> 00:37:02.121
- You!
- Wait!

00:37:21.172 --> 00:37:23.913
I'm really annoyed too

00:37:23.913 --> 00:37:25.872
in this situation.

00:37:32.867 --> 00:37:37.475
[Kangseng Bookstore]

00:37:44.438 --> 00:37:46.072
Tae Joo!

00:37:49.172 --> 00:37:51.205
Why did you go there?

00:37:51.205 --> 00:37:53.005
Why did I go where?

00:38:03.005 --> 00:38:06.072
So I'm supposed to just
watch those students get beaten?

00:38:06.072 --> 00:38:08.072
You might get hurt.

00:38:08.872 --> 00:38:11.538
If I see you at a place like that again,

00:38:11.538 --> 00:38:14.138
I'll lock you up then.

00:38:14.138 --> 00:38:15.938
Remember that.

00:38:29.372 --> 00:38:31.405
A sting operation?

00:38:31.405 --> 00:38:33.138
[Investigation Team 2]
Yes.

00:38:33.138 --> 00:38:35.072
The plan is simple.

00:38:35.938 --> 00:38:38.405
We draw the suspect out
from wherever he's hiding

00:38:39.705 --> 00:38:41.838
onto the street.

00:38:43.938 --> 00:38:47.405
So you're suggesting
a female officer as bait.

00:38:47.405 --> 00:38:50.605
- Yes, exactly.
- But how do we know where he'll show up?

00:38:52.772 --> 00:38:56.205
As you know, he's got weapon.

00:38:56.205 --> 00:38:59.638
No one knows what might happen
during the operation.

00:38:59.638 --> 00:39:02.505
Anyone who doesn't want in can step out.

00:39:10.972 --> 00:39:14.672
Sir, we're police too.

00:39:14.672 --> 00:39:17.872
We really want to catch the suspect.

00:39:17.872 --> 00:39:19.505
Me too!

00:39:31.772 --> 00:39:34.338
One woman and two men.

00:39:34.338 --> 00:39:37.172
Each team will consist of
at least three people.

00:39:48.472 --> 00:39:52.505
The suspect has a habit of
disguising himself as a scarecrow.

00:39:53.638 --> 00:39:55.788
If you see a scarecrow,

00:39:55.788 --> 00:39:57.705
be sure to check it.

00:40:37.338 --> 00:40:39.172
Good work.

00:40:42.505 --> 00:40:44.305
Miss!

00:40:44.305 --> 00:40:47.838
- Oh, Hye Jin!
- Kook Hee was taken away in an ambulance!

00:40:47.838 --> 00:40:50.472
She was hit by a motorcycle
in front of the school.

00:40:50.472 --> 00:40:53.605
- Which hospital?
- Probably Jeil Hospital nearby.

00:40:53.605 --> 00:40:54.638
Let's take my car.

00:40:54.638 --> 00:40:56.338
- Okay.
- Come here.

00:40:56.338 --> 00:40:59.075
Let's go home. My goodness.

00:40:59.075 --> 00:41:03.235
Hey, come with me!

00:41:03.235 --> 00:41:05.150
Let's go!

00:41:14.605 --> 00:41:16.205
Sun Young...

00:41:25.472 --> 00:41:27.241
Thank goodness,

00:41:27.241 --> 00:41:29.238
it didn't get any worse.

00:41:29.238 --> 00:41:30.272
It's a relief.

00:41:30.272 --> 00:41:32.705
She'll be discharged soon.

00:41:32.705 --> 00:41:34.805
I'll drive you back.

00:41:34.805 --> 00:41:36.038
It's okay. No need.

00:41:36.038 --> 00:41:38.972
Come on. We're going the same way anyway.

00:41:40.005 --> 00:41:41.638
Well, then...

00:41:53.205 --> 00:41:55.272
[Closed]

00:41:59.038 --> 00:42:01.838
Why does he keep blowing up the phone?

00:42:01.838 --> 00:42:06.238
He said Sun Young got into
some guy's car and went away.

00:42:06.238 --> 00:42:07.238
What?

00:42:07.238 --> 00:42:08.238
What kind of car?

00:42:08.238 --> 00:42:10.438
A Grandeur.

00:42:10.438 --> 00:42:12.672
Pretty nice.

00:42:12.672 --> 00:42:15.772
Sun Young isn't the type to go for money.

00:42:15.772 --> 00:42:18.405
She cares about looks.

00:42:18.405 --> 00:42:21.305
Oh, come on.

00:42:21.305 --> 00:42:24.538
My mother always says
beauty doesn't last a few years anyway.

00:42:24.538 --> 00:42:26.938
You can't live off looks.

00:42:28.672 --> 00:42:30.672
There must be a reason.

00:42:32.405 --> 00:42:34.372
Don't you trust Sun Young?

00:42:35.072 --> 00:42:36.705
That's not it.

00:42:38.505 --> 00:42:40.105
Hey,

00:42:40.105 --> 00:42:42.005
who took this out?

00:42:43.072 --> 00:42:44.405
What's that drawing?

00:42:44.405 --> 00:42:46.938
Don't touch other people's things!

00:42:46.938 --> 00:42:49.072
A customer left it behind.

00:43:02.972 --> 00:43:06.605
[Kangseng Police Station]

00:43:08.872 --> 00:43:11.505
Ms. Lee, you're off today's operation.

00:43:11.505 --> 00:43:14.538
No, it's okay. I can do it.

00:43:14.538 --> 00:43:15.657
You can't even walk properly,

00:43:15.657 --> 00:43:17.638
- so how would you do it?
- But...

00:43:17.638 --> 00:43:19.072
Just stay.

00:43:19.072 --> 00:43:20.705
I can do it.

00:43:20.705 --> 00:43:22.305
Have a seat.

00:43:26.172 --> 00:43:28.672
Then what about our team today?

00:43:28.672 --> 00:43:30.305
Mr. Park.

00:43:30.972 --> 00:43:33.038
Want to try wearing a skirt?

00:43:34.272 --> 00:43:36.072
It might suit you.

00:43:36.072 --> 00:43:37.872
That's a bit...

00:43:40.805 --> 00:43:42.405
Hey!

00:43:43.705 --> 00:43:44.838
Got a substitute.

00:43:44.838 --> 00:43:46.472
A substitute?

00:43:47.538 --> 00:43:49.172
I'll do it.

00:43:50.038 --> 00:43:51.472
I did good, right?

00:43:51.472 --> 00:43:54.105
Mr. Heo, did you forget
this operation is classified?

00:43:54.105 --> 00:43:57.105
She agreed to keep it confidential.

00:43:57.105 --> 00:43:59.838
Mr. Heo, how can you trust a reporter...

00:43:59.838 --> 00:44:01.505
Ouch!

00:44:01.505 --> 00:44:04.505
You!

00:44:04.505 --> 00:44:05.838
Take me off if you want.

00:44:05.838 --> 00:44:09.072
I'll blow this wide open
in tomorrow's papers.

00:44:10.938 --> 00:44:13.072
Sorry.

00:44:13.072 --> 00:44:14.272
It's fine.

00:44:14.272 --> 00:44:16.338
Don't wear stockings.

00:44:18.305 --> 00:44:21.572
And Seo Ji Won, you listen carefully.

00:44:23.205 --> 00:44:25.605
When you're out there,

00:44:25.605 --> 00:44:30.772
if you see anything suspicious
like a scarecrow, run away immediately.

00:44:30.772 --> 00:44:33.005
Suspicious scarecrow?

00:44:34.272 --> 00:44:36.272
It might be the suspect.

00:44:47.605 --> 00:44:51.005
Wow, your place is really close to mine.

00:44:51.005 --> 00:44:53.805
From now on, ride in my car, okay?

00:44:53.805 --> 00:44:55.872
No, thank you. But I appreciate the thought.

00:44:55.872 --> 00:44:58.205
Why? The streets are scary
at night these days.

00:44:58.205 --> 00:45:00.972
My fiancé picks me up
every day, so it's fine.

00:45:01.738 --> 00:45:04.105
Oh, you are getting married?

00:45:04.105 --> 00:45:05.705
Yes.

00:45:05.705 --> 00:45:07.605
Congratulations.

00:45:09.405 --> 00:45:11.205
What kind of family is he from?

00:45:11.205 --> 00:45:14.089
Just an ordinary family.

00:45:14.705 --> 00:45:17.005
Then, does his family know

00:45:17.005 --> 00:45:19.105
about your mother?

00:45:22.672 --> 00:45:24.305
Pardon?

00:45:25.805 --> 00:45:29.572
I'm not trying to pry. It just came up.

00:45:29.572 --> 00:45:31.072
Oh dear, don't worry.

00:45:31.072 --> 00:45:33.538
I won't tell anyone about this.

00:45:33.538 --> 00:45:35.872
I'm good at keeping my mouth shut.

00:45:37.772 --> 00:45:40.572
So who do you take after, Sun Young?

00:45:40.572 --> 00:45:42.838
Your mother?

00:45:42.838 --> 00:45:44.772
Oh, right?

00:45:44.772 --> 00:45:47.438
You must have gotten your pretty face
from your mother.

00:45:47.438 --> 00:45:49.172
Let me out.

00:45:50.672 --> 00:45:52.872
Why all of a sudden?
You're making this awkward.

00:45:52.872 --> 00:45:55.305
Let me out. I'm uncomfortable.

00:45:55.305 --> 00:45:57.872
What did I even do to make you uncomfortable?

00:46:02.705 --> 00:46:04.138
Sun Young.

00:46:04.138 --> 00:46:06.772
Is that what you think of me?

00:46:10.672 --> 00:46:13.205
That's insulting.

00:46:13.205 --> 00:46:16.172
I'm not someone
who deserves to be treated like that.

00:46:16.172 --> 00:46:18.038
Do you even know
what kind of family I come from?

00:46:18.038 --> 00:46:19.272
Do you know who my uncle is?

00:46:19.272 --> 00:46:20.405
Calm down and stop the car!

00:46:20.405 --> 00:46:21.505
Who are you to give orders?

00:46:21.505 --> 00:46:23.172
You, daughter of a tramp!

00:46:24.172 --> 00:46:25.405
Stop the car now!

00:46:25.405 --> 00:46:26.472
Let go!

00:46:26.472 --> 00:46:28.205
Stop the car!

00:46:29.638 --> 00:46:31.638
Hey, let go!

00:47:00.227 --> 00:47:02.025
You wench! Get over here.

00:48:42.405 --> 00:48:45.472
Oh, it's chilly.

00:48:45.472 --> 00:48:48.505
Why did he insist on no stockings?

00:51:09.538 --> 00:51:11.372
A scarecrow...

00:51:11.372 --> 00:51:12.705
There was a scarecrow.

00:51:12.705 --> 00:51:17.138
And I think I heard stray dogs too.

00:51:17.138 --> 00:51:19.138
Stray dogs.

00:51:19.138 --> 00:51:20.738
No way.

00:51:26.072 --> 00:51:27.505
When you're out there,

00:51:27.505 --> 00:51:31.105
if you see anything suspicious
like a scarecrow, run away immediately.

00:51:31.105 --> 00:51:32.872
Suspicious scarecrow?

00:51:32.872 --> 00:51:34.838
It might be the suspect.

00:52:25.738 --> 00:52:26.938
Police.

00:52:26.938 --> 00:52:28.205
It's okay. Calm down.

00:52:28.205 --> 00:52:29.705
Police, police.

00:52:29.705 --> 00:52:31.405
I'm police.

00:52:34.672 --> 00:52:37.605
It's okay now, it's okay.

00:52:37.605 --> 00:52:39.305
You're safe now.

00:52:40.805 --> 00:52:42.705
Where did that punk go?

00:52:46.105 --> 00:52:47.105
Where is he?

00:52:47.105 --> 00:52:48.472
Why are you here?

00:52:48.472 --> 00:52:49.938
- Where is Ji Won?
- She's not here?

00:52:49.938 --> 00:52:52.205
That's him!

00:52:53.872 --> 00:52:55.672
Mr. Park, look after her
and go to the car first.

00:52:55.672 --> 00:52:56.672
Report our location.

00:52:56.672 --> 00:52:58.272
Yes, sir.

00:53:50.972 --> 00:53:52.605
Ji Won!

00:53:53.372 --> 00:53:55.005
Seo Ji Won!

00:53:57.405 --> 00:54:00.572
Seo Ji Won! Answer me!

00:54:00.572 --> 00:54:02.205
Seo Ji Won!

00:54:12.038 --> 00:54:14.105
Ji Won!

00:54:14.105 --> 00:54:16.305
Ji Won!

00:54:16.305 --> 00:54:18.072
Ji Won, wake up!

00:54:18.072 --> 00:54:19.172
Seo Ji Won!

00:54:19.172 --> 00:54:20.438
Ji Won!

00:54:20.438 --> 00:54:22.005
Hey, stay with me!

00:54:22.005 --> 00:54:25.105
Hey, Ji Won. Seo Ji Won!

00:54:30.205 --> 00:54:31.838
Ji Won!

00:54:57.772 --> 00:55:01.472
The surgery went well,
but whether there's brain damage is still...

00:55:17.405 --> 00:55:19.005
Tae Joo.

00:55:19.705 --> 00:55:22.872
I'll stay here, so you should...

00:55:23.972 --> 00:55:25.838
I think you should go.

00:55:25.838 --> 00:55:28.405
Where should I go?

00:55:29.205 --> 00:55:31.305
Hey.

00:55:31.305 --> 00:55:32.905
Your sister

00:55:34.338 --> 00:55:36.172
is in this hospital.

00:55:40.405 --> 00:55:42.038
Sun Young...

00:55:49.763 --> 00:55:52.003
[Kang Sun Young]

00:56:01.105 --> 00:56:02.738
Sun Young!

00:56:06.138 --> 00:56:07.972
What on earth...

00:56:14.572 --> 00:56:16.572
Still no word?

00:56:18.038 --> 00:56:21.605
Wait, have you checked everywhere
he might've gone?

00:56:25.138 --> 00:56:27.272
That's...

00:56:27.272 --> 00:56:28.872
Sir.

00:56:30.372 --> 00:56:31.505
Do you have time?

00:56:31.505 --> 00:56:34.672
Yeah, I'll call you later.

00:56:35.472 --> 00:56:36.738
I have something important to tell you...

00:56:36.738 --> 00:56:38.305
Oh, come on!

00:56:38.305 --> 00:56:41.505
What on earth could be so urgent
for you to make this big a fuss over?

00:56:44.638 --> 00:56:46.272
Sir.

00:56:47.038 --> 00:56:48.905
It will only take a moment.

00:57:32.105 --> 00:57:33.572
Hey, you punk!

00:57:33.572 --> 00:57:35.945
Relax, relax!

00:57:35.945 --> 00:57:37.072
Listen.

00:57:37.072 --> 00:57:38.838
Hey, lift your head.

00:57:38.838 --> 00:57:41.038
Relax!

00:57:41.038 --> 00:57:42.738
You punk!

00:57:42.738 --> 00:57:44.372
Hyeon Cheol!

00:57:46.405 --> 00:57:47.572
Hyeon Cheol!

00:57:47.572 --> 00:57:49.772
Hyeon Cheol, stay with me!

00:57:49.772 --> 00:57:51.405
Hyeon Cheol!

00:57:52.338 --> 00:57:53.538
Dad...

00:57:53.538 --> 00:57:55.177
Yeah,

00:57:55.177 --> 00:57:56.805
I'm here.

00:57:56.805 --> 00:58:00.305
What on earth happened here?

00:58:00.305 --> 00:58:03.505
I told you to make some time for me, sir.

00:58:06.038 --> 00:58:08.072
Was it you?

00:58:08.072 --> 00:58:09.738
You're the one who did this to my son?

00:58:09.738 --> 00:58:13.038
Sir, it's not about Hyeon Cheol
getting hit a few times.

00:58:14.672 --> 00:58:16.572
Did you know

00:58:16.572 --> 00:58:21.672
your son committed a serious violation
of the National Security Law?

00:58:22.538 --> 00:58:24.438
What?

00:58:24.438 --> 00:58:26.838
If you knew and turned a blind eye,

00:58:27.572 --> 00:58:30.438
this won't be something
we can contain within the prosecution.

00:58:31.572 --> 00:58:33.205
You punk!

00:58:41.038 --> 00:58:43.305
Is it true the serial killer showed up today?

00:58:43.305 --> 00:58:44.872
Has he been caught yet?

00:58:44.872 --> 00:58:46.638
Let's leave before this gets any louder.

00:58:46.638 --> 00:58:48.438
Jeez, how did things end up like this?

00:58:48.438 --> 00:58:50.805
So she's the daughter of a bar madam.

00:58:50.805 --> 00:58:53.072
I'm quite shocked as well.

00:59:01.059 --> 00:59:02.562
- Hey!
- Stop!

00:59:04.835 --> 00:59:06.438
- Stop it!
- What's going on?

00:59:06.438 --> 00:59:09.272
Hey, what are you doing?
Hold back the reporters!

00:59:09.272 --> 00:59:11.338
Block them!

00:59:12.772 --> 00:59:15.205
Someone help!

00:59:15.205 --> 00:59:16.705
- Hey, you punk!
- Stop it!

00:59:16.705 --> 00:59:20.489
[Police officer arrested
for assaulting an active teacher]

00:59:22.072 --> 00:59:23.872
What are you going to do about this?

00:59:24.538 --> 00:59:27.238
Why are you targeting innocent people
instead of the real criminal?

00:59:27.238 --> 00:59:28.805
He's not exactly innocent.

00:59:28.805 --> 00:59:29.872
What?

00:59:29.872 --> 00:59:31.672
But arresting Detective Kang?

00:59:31.672 --> 00:59:34.305
How can you arrest someone
before an investigation?

00:59:34.305 --> 00:59:36.205
Why not? He got caught red-handed.

00:59:36.205 --> 00:59:40.038
After what happened to his sister,
what kind of brother wouldn't lose it?

00:59:40.038 --> 00:59:42.238
So what, a police officer
can just beat a civilian?

00:59:42.238 --> 00:59:44.172
And even in front of reporters?

00:59:49.372 --> 00:59:55.238
The prosecutor in charge already
issued the arrest warrant, so what can we do?

01:00:02.338 --> 01:00:04.172
- Officer Jeong.
- Yes.

01:00:04.172 --> 01:00:06.505
Let me use the phone, quickly.

01:00:06.505 --> 01:00:08.072
Come on, quickly.

01:00:08.072 --> 01:00:09.172
No, you can't.

01:00:09.172 --> 01:00:10.505
Bring it now!

01:00:10.505 --> 01:00:12.005
Bring it, come here, Ji Hwan.

01:00:12.005 --> 01:00:13.105
Hurry up.

01:00:13.105 --> 01:00:14.472
I really can't.

01:00:14.472 --> 01:00:16.172
It's fine.

01:00:16.172 --> 01:00:17.772
Bring it here. Darn it.

01:00:20.672 --> 01:00:22.305
I'll be quick.

01:00:24.705 --> 01:00:28.072
This is a total mess.

01:00:28.072 --> 01:00:29.705
Hey, bring it here!

01:00:30.338 --> 01:00:31.938
Put the phone down.

01:00:31.938 --> 01:00:33.638
I'll be quick.

01:00:33.638 --> 01:00:35.238
Sorry, Mr. Kang.

01:00:45.338 --> 01:00:47.005
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

01:00:47.005 --> 01:00:49.705
There's a critical patient.

01:00:49.705 --> 01:00:51.972
I just need to check the patient's condition.

01:00:52.672 --> 01:00:55.905
Calling won't wake her up.

01:00:57.605 --> 01:00:59.872
Go get questioned.

01:00:59.872 --> 01:01:00.872
On what?

01:01:00.872 --> 01:01:04.705
The assault on Jeon Kyeong Ho.
That's my jurisdiction.

01:01:08.072 --> 01:01:09.438
Jeez.

01:01:09.438 --> 01:01:12.305
Are you seriously
going to lock me up over that?

01:01:12.305 --> 01:01:16.038
You think the case is going
to be handed to you now?

01:01:17.705 --> 01:01:19.938
It's already mine.

01:01:19.938 --> 01:01:21.372
What?

01:01:21.372 --> 01:01:23.205
I told you.

01:01:23.205 --> 01:01:25.605
I'd take it back.

01:01:25.605 --> 01:01:28.405
You, and the case.

01:01:53.605 --> 01:01:55.338
He still hasn't come?

01:01:57.238 --> 01:02:00.438
Well, he's exercising.

01:02:00.438 --> 01:02:01.472
Exercising?

01:02:01.472 --> 01:02:06.038
Yes, inmate 1045
has a morning exercise routine.

01:02:06.038 --> 01:02:09.905
He'll be done soon, so please wait a little.

01:02:10.938 --> 01:02:13.272
Lee Yong Woo is sure diligent.

01:02:14.338 --> 01:02:15.938
He's like that about everything.

01:02:15.938 --> 01:02:19.238
Health, woodworking, all of it.

01:02:21.972 --> 01:02:23.572
I see.

01:02:27.872 --> 01:02:30.538
Oh dear, I'm a little late...

01:02:31.272 --> 01:02:32.338
Where did he go?

01:02:32.338 --> 01:02:34.272
- Gone.
- Gone?

01:02:34.272 --> 01:02:37.005
Yes, he said he'd come tomorrow afternoon.

01:02:37.005 --> 01:02:39.072
So it doesn't interfere
with your workout routine.

01:02:47.605 --> 01:02:49.738
Let's go, officer.

01:03:28.572 --> 01:03:30.872
Detective Kang Tae Joo is being removed
from all investigations, effective today.

01:03:30.872 --> 01:03:33.305
Let's just take his resignation
quietly and end it.

01:03:33.305 --> 01:03:34.305
Don't worry.

01:03:34.305 --> 01:03:36.938
I don't care about means or methods, either.

01:03:36.938 --> 01:03:38.838
Do you really have to quit being a cop?

01:03:38.838 --> 01:03:41.105
[Kangseng Bookstore]
Just catch him for me, sir.

01:03:41.105 --> 01:03:42.838
Any last words?

01:03:42.838 --> 01:03:44.438
Make sure to catch that punk

01:03:44.438 --> 01:03:46.405
before he kills anyone else.

01:03:48.505 --> 01:03:49.505
Sir!

01:03:49.505 --> 01:03:51.238
Well, the body... It's another murder.

01:03:51.238 --> 01:03:52.838
We found it!